    // But since each element has 3 choices, we need a ternary mask.
    // To represent ternary mask, we can use two bits per element, but it's complex.
    // Alternatively, we can iterate through all possible subsets for A and B, ensuring they are disjoint.

    // But for n=19, even this is 3^19 which is too large.
